<br>
Avrus your very last statement was quite the valid one.  But thats a 2 way street.  Not many people can organize a raid at the drop of a hat.  Thats why they tend to take advantage of when they have the numbers.  Wether someone has posted itr or not.  ITR is a list system, like a train schedule.  <br>
<br>
Fear is cleared by guild a, guild b plans to clear fear 14 hours later when they have the numbers present.  In the meanwhile guild c decides to clear fear 9 hours after it was cleared by uber guild a. Guild b gets upset, but doesn't realize that guild c has done exactly what guild b wanted to do they just did it when it was convient for them.<br>
<br>
ITR often eliminates the possiblities of other raids taking place due to repop times and such.  ITR has its problems and so does 1c1s,  with over 20+ guilds planes capable, these problems will never go away til verant decides to fix them or until their are enough planes were each guild could occupy 1 at the same time.  The best thing anyone can do is suck it up and move on, not that thats always an easy thing to do.<br>
<br>
</font><P><b>Ghetto Heaven Resident</b><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E9E9EF><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uavrus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avrus</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>MithMarr Squire<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star.gif></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>23</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>3/24/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>7:40:12 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.winterblood.com/graphics/forumgraphics/icon_flames.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: ITR is not a list system.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">In fact, what an ITR system does is level the playing field against larger guilds.<br>
<br>
NOT having an ITR system favors larger guilds, and crushes smaller guilds.<br>
<br>
I've been around for a long time, and so far IMHO ITR is by far the best system around.<br>
<br>
List systems suck. They typically involve unorganized paper lists maybe recorded, maybe not. It typically involves you sitting around for 30 minutes or maybe an hour. Possibly getting a group, possibly not.<br>
<br>
All an ITR system does is say &quot;Hey, we'll be raiding on such and such a day ... it would be polite for you not to be there at the same time.&quot;<br>
<br>
</font><P><img src="http://www.telusplanet.net/public/jreiner/images/avrussig.jpg"></a><BR>
