<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#e9e9ef><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/udelnathapowa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delnatha Powa</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>MithMarr Squire<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star.gif></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>26</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>3/26/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>4:41:44 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.winterblood.com/graphics/forumgraphics/icon_flames.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: ITR is not a list system.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">&quot;When you read the side of the EQ box, an EZboard account isn't listed as a requirement under processor speed and video card&quot;  --my original quote<br>
<br>
&quot;Heh, Del, very true.. Very very true, well, it doesn't say on my &quot;Box-O-Life&quot; I have to be kind and curtious, it doesn't say I have to open the door for ladies. It doesn't say I have to help little old women across the street, it doesn't say I have to volunteer 20 hours a week to helping the orphans here near the base I work at in Italy. Nope, but I do that, why? Because it's a mature, kind, and Honorable thing to do. And I feel rewarded when I, one of the &quot;haves&quot; see a smile on one of the &quot;have nots.&quot; So, if you want to go by the Box, go right ahead, I feel sorry for the lonely and greed-filled life you have in EQ. I'm not sorry I don't have the p#@t l3wT you have, but that's not what fulfills my life. Friends, Family, and Honor.&quot;  <br>
--Calizor<br>
<br>
Ok...I read that about 18 times and am trying really hard not to see it as a personal insult directed against me...but since Weylin already flamed you for it, and you apologized for it a couple times already, I'll just let it go but, yes, it hurts a little.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of different ways raids could be scheduled for EQ...the most common is messageboards but it could be chat rooms, IRC, emails, whatever...the bottom line is you do not need any of them to play EQ.  Does it make you a bad, evil, greedy person if you don't have an EZboard account?  No.  You can still log on, have fun, play the game, make friends, join raids, etc.  That is the simple point and the only point I was making.<br>
<br>
I have characters in both Afterlife and Adamantine Kinship.  I spend a lot of time helping people, pulling corpses of people I don't know out of bad spots and trying to find them a res...giving away my old &quot;p#@t l3wT&quot; (your term, not mine) to people who I think deserve and could benefit from it, and generally helping where needed.  I do this not just for my guild but for others as well because the bottom line is Afterlife members don't need a lot of help with most things and I have a sense of reward from helping others who aren't as fortunate as I am.  Now, I don't help orphans 20 hours a week but basically, like most people I am sure, I am a similar person in RL to the way I play my character.  Friends, family, honor...these are all things which are also important to me.  All that the EQ box says is what you have to have to play the game.  Whether you have a system that supports EQ and whether you have an EZboard account or not has nothing to do with the quality of person you are.  What exactly does your &quot;Box-O-Life&quot; say and not say anyway Calizor?  I'm curious what you mean by that?<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm tired and need sleep...no idea if this makes any sense or not but this is the first time I checked back here since my first post.  Look at the Afterlife people who have posted here including officers and see how many first posts there are here.  As a whole we just do not do as much with messageboards as most other guilds.  Does this mean we don't care about others?  Why don't you talk to us or group with us in the actual game before you make that presumption?<br>
<br>
