<br>
Now, our ideas of fun, may be slightly different, but the end result is the same.  For us to tell you how to play your game, or vice versa is just ludicrous.  These boards are just an enhancement of the game, not required, but a nice addition.  Something that helps us accomplish things, something that is entertaining outside the game, yet is still part of the game.<br>
<br>
The paragraph you quoted me was a &quot;self expression&quot; paragraph about UBERguilds in general... not at yourself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  That's what I tried to explain afterword.  I used &quot;you&quot; and the such over and over and it could have very easily been taken as a flame and it may have even been started as one, but it was a general comment.  We at MMDN have been flamed by UBERguilds for supposedly &quot;holding a gun&quot; to peoples heads and making them use our system and no other system is right.  These UBERguilds fight, tooth and nail, to make us think 1C1S system is the &quot;only right way&quot; but even when we are right in being there (Forming at the Fear Gate, clearing Fear and there's an unexpected 'repop') according to the ITR <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> AND</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> beliefs, they make up a new set of rules.<br>
<br>
Cal<br>
